In recent years, the urbanization of the country has accelerated the pace of urbanization,
the urban population has grown dramatically, and the city’s traffic has grown in size, making
urban transportation face enormous challenges. Which parking is difficult, parking expensive
is one of the biggest car troubles in the city. With the rise of the "shared concept" and
"sharing economy" in recent years, a shared parking system has been introduced. Through the
Internet and big data, the shortage of parking spaces, unbalanced use, inefficient use, and non-
transparent parking information are not shared. To help improve the city's traffic conditions
and increase the efficiency of the use of facilities.
The system uses Java programming language, combined with ORACLE database
technology, while the public end adopts HTML5 technology, the back office management
system adopts JEESITE open source framework, and the interface service adopts SPRING
BOOT and SPRING CLOUD integrated micro service framework, which can well support
distributed applications. . This article discusses in detail a shared parking system that we
designed and implemented based on B/S structure and J2EE platform framework. The system
is designed using OOA object-oriented analysis methods and OOD object-oriented design
methods, based on the UML unified modeling language for business modeling of the system
to develop a truly feasible system design. We first completed the analysis of the needs of the
system through the actual business needs of users and the analysis of shared parking business
processes. The public number terminal system is mainly for users to provide basic
information collection, appointment parking spaces, order inquiries and other functions,
mainly include: user registration landing, reservation parking spaces, my orders, personal
center, real name authentication + network sign module, for users and the The interaction of
the website communicates. The backstage is mainly to provide various functions for the
administrator to manage and maintain the website. The main modules are: user and authority
management, mobile terminal user information query, parking management, parking space
release and audit, parking space reservation query and audit, payment channel information
